<div class="timelinebackground">

     <div style="border:20px; border-style:double; border-color:rgb(0,0,100); padding:15px; margin-left:250px; margin-right:190px; background-color:rgb(160,180,200);">
       <h1 id="Timeline"><b>Timeline</b></h1>
      <div class="timeline"><ul>
        <li><b>1843:</b> Edvard Grieg was born in the city of Bergen.</li>
        <li><b>1858:</b> Grieg enrolled at the conservatory in Leipzig concentrating on the piano.</li>
        <li><b>1860:</b> Grieg survived two life-threatening lung conditions pleurisy and tuberculosis which left his health impaired for the rest of his life.</li>
        <li><b>1861:</b> Grieg made his debut as a pianist in Karishmn, Sweden.</li>
        <li><b>1863:</b> Grieg went to Copenhagen where he stayed for three years and met Danish composers J.P.E. Hartmann and Niels Gade.</li>
        <li><b>1867:</b> Grieg married Nina Hagerup.</li>
        <li><b>1868:</b> Grieg composed his piano concerto in A minor in the summer of 1868.</li>
        <li><b>1870:</b> Grieg met Franz Liszt in Italy.</li>
        <li><b>1874:</b> Grieg began his compositions of the incidental music for Henrik Ibsen’s play Peer Gynt at the request of the author</li>
        <li><b>1880:</b> Grieg became the musical director of the Bergen Philharmonic.
          </li>
        <li><b>1888:</b> Grieg met Tchaikovsky in Leipzig.</li>
        <li><b>1907:</b> Grieg died of heart failure in Bergen in the late summer of 1907.</li>
        </ul></div>

</div>


